sentences: Phyllis Weliver (born September 28, 1968) is an American academic specializing in Victorian literature and music history.
In 2011, Weliver became a lifetime Fellow of Gladstone's Library in Wales.
She received a National Endowment for the Humanities Fellowship in 2015, and a National Endowment for the Humanities Summer Stipend in 2004.
